\f0\fs18 \cf0 \
Use controls, which most often are defined as arguments in a ugenGraphFunc, to give information to a synth, either when it is created and/or after it is running. Supply default values to the arguments to make code more readable and to protect against user error (such as forgetting to supply a value to an argument).\
\
(\cf4 \
\cf5 // 3 arguments (controls) with default values\cf4 \
\cf6 SynthDef\cf4 (\
	\cf7 "withControls"\cf4 , \
	\{ \cf6 arg\cf4  freq = 440, beatFreq = 1, mul = 0.22;\
	\cf6 Out\cf4 .ar(\
		0,\
		\cf6 SinOsc\cf4 .ar([freq, freq+beatFreq], 0, mul)\
	)\
\}).load(s);\
\cf0 )\
\cf4 \
\cf5 // items in the array are passed to the controls in Synth when it's created\cf4 \
z = \cf6 Synth\cf4 (\cf7 "withControls"\cf4 , [\cf8 \\freq\cf4 , 440, \cf8 \\beatFreq\cf4 , 1, \cf8 \\mul\cf4 , 0.1]);\
\
\cf5 // evaluate this line after the synth is running to reset its controls\cf4 \
z.set(\cf8 \\freq\cf4 , 700, \cf8 \\beatFreq\cf4 , 2, \cf8 \\mul\cf4 , 0.2);\
\
\cf0 \
\cf3 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////\cf0 \
\
